<DOC><DOCNO> AP891102-0164 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-02-89 2126EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Pentagon-Pakistan     11-02 0152</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Pentagon-Pakistan,150</SECOND><TEXT>   Pentagon Tells Congress of Arms Sale to Pakistan</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Pentagon informed Congress on Thursdaythat Pakistan intends to buy four Phalanx weapons systems, a typeof Gatling gun used as a last-ditch defense against anti-shipmissiles.   The estimated cost of the five-inch gun systems, which alsoinclude ammunition, logistical support and training, amounts to $29million, the Pentagon said in a statement.   The weapons will provide a surface-to-air defensive capabilityfor frigates in the Pakistani Navy and will be in addition to theearlier versions of the weapons systems that have been delivered totheir forces, the Pentagon said.   The Pentagon also said that Pakistan intends to buy 13Firefinder counter-mortar radar sets, 26 AN@VRC-46 radios andlogistical support at a cost of $65 million.   The sale of both types of equipment will not affect the basicmilitary balance in the region, the Pentagon statement said.</TEXT></DOC>